      <paragraph>
        <num>89.</num>
        <content>
          <p>The cost-optimal technology and energy mix is more affected by the uncertainty arising from technology and resource availability than by the choice of the sixth carbon budget level. All pathways at least double current electricity generation by 2050 and rely on substantial hydrogen production and biomass use. However, the final energy mix is highly variable depending on the modelling assumptions. The table below summarises the modelled range of energy use. </p>
        </content>
